## SDD mode (merge into orchestrator)

Add to your orchestrator's classify table:

| **SDD** | "Start SDD", "Continue SDD", "spec this feature", "speckit", "SDD", "sdd", "sdd-remote", "spec-driven", new multi-step feature when `.specify/` exists |

Add routing block:

**SDD** (Spec-Driven Development — see repo SDD user guide)
- Entry = `.cursor/skills/sdd-entry/SKILL.md` only (Start SDD / Continue SDD). Never invoke bare `speckit-*` as the top-level skill.
- Every phase goes through **`sdd-orchestrator`** + **`sdd-ctl`** (plan → worker → hooks → judge/swarm → record). Worker procedure = matching `speckit-*` skill. Workers never write `phase-exits.md`.
- Resolve `FEATURE_DIR` (`specs/NNN-*`) + next `PHASE`, then run the orchestrator for that phase (`auto_chain` from chat; `single_phase` from Spec Kit workflows).
- Phase order: specify → **clarify** (before plan) → plan → tasks → **analyze** (before implement if 3+ boundaries) → implement → **confidence**.
- Passing phases auto-continue. Failures repair up to the configured cap, then stop. Optional `"gate_mode": "interactive"` in `.specify/orchestrator.json` pauses after pass.
- Do not skip clarify before plan; do not implement without `tasks.md`.
- Quality gates: `{LINT_CMD}` and `{TEST_CMD}` (also via `.specify/orchestrator.json` `implement_hooks` when `allow_repo_commands: true`).
- CLI: `specify workflow run sdd` (flags: `scope`, `stop_at`, `issues`, `mode`) or `sdd-remote`. Alias workflow IDs are removed — use flags ([deprecated-aliases.md](../spec-kit/deprecated-aliases.md)).
- On compact/checkpoint during SDD: include `tasks.md` progress (completed/total) in handoff.

Requires global `~/.cursor/skills/sdd-orchestrator/` (symlink) + clone of [sdd-orchestrator](https://github.com/Wade-O-Lution-Inc/sdd-orchestrator) at `~/.cursor/sdd-orchestrator-ctl/` — see [day1-setup.md](../../day1-setup.md).

Reference: [meeting_notes_workflow/.cursor/rules/00-orchestrator.mdc](https://github.com/Wade-O-Lution-Inc/meeting_notes_workflow/blob/main/.cursor/rules/00-orchestrator.mdc)
